    with ({});
  };
  void [typeof this, typeof this, typeof this, typeof this];
};
```

Adds a variable declaration in the global scope.

``` javascript
void [typeof this, typeof this, typeof this, typeof this];
```

`this` could be consolidated in the global scope by employing a closure (if it results in less source characters).

``` bash
uglifyjs -c <<ENDH
void [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null];
with ({});
void [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null];
ENDH
```

